Too often the solution is overcomplicated with terms like
- DP
- Kadane Algorithm

You can solve this problem with only simple logical reasoning to come up with the optimal solution.

Our input: [7,1,5,3,6,4]

We know:
-  You can potentially sell stock on any day
-  When we sell stock on a certain day, we want to have bought stock when it was at it's lowest prior to that day

We can simulate selling selling the stock every day and see which day would yield the max profit.

We do this by going through the array day by day while:
- Keeping track of lowest value
- Simulating the maximum profit if we were to sold that day

```
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
        int lowestUntilThisPoint = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int maxProfit = -1;

        for (int price: prices) {
            if (price < lowestUntilThisPoint) {
                lowestUntilThisPoint = price;
            }
            int profit = price - lowestUntilThisPoint;
            if (profit > maxProfit) 
                maxProfit = profit;
        }
        return Math.max(maxProfit, 0);
    }
}
```

