	* stocks are bought at price[i] and sold at price[j], where i < j, and 
	* profit = price[j] - price[i] is max across all profits
* So scan from left to right, recording any profit and also the cheapest price seen yet
* If you come across a profit, check if its more than last profit, if yes, then this is the new max profit
* If you come across a cheaper price than the last cheapest seen, then this is the new cheapest price
>**T/S:** O(n)/O(1), where n = size(nums)
```
public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
	var maxProfit = 0;

	for (int i = 1, cheapest = prices[0]; i < prices.length; i++) {
		if (prices[i] >= cheapest)
			maxProfit = Math.max(maxProfit, prices[i] - cheapest);
		cheapest = Math.min(cheapest, prices[i]);
	}
	return maxProfit;
}
```
