# Intuition
To use **2-pointer** method to solve the stock buy sell problem.

# Approach
we take two variables **l** and **r** that we given the 0th and 1st index.
we traverse the while loop till the array length.
when we get the price of **right index greater than the left index** we find out the profit.
then we check if the profit it greater than maxp then we switch them by using **Math.max** fucntion.

if the right index value is not greater than the left index value than we appoint left as right, (l = r).

then we increment the value of right pointer(r++) and the while loop goes on till the end.

at the end of while loop we can get the value of maximum profit.
# Solution

```
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
		int l = 0 , r = 1;
        int maxp = 0;
        int profit = 0;
        while (r < prices.length){
            if(prices[l] < prices[r]){
                profit = prices[r] - prices[l];
                maxp = Math.max(maxp,profit);
            }
            else{
                l = r;
            }
            r++;
        }
        return maxp;
    }
}
```

# Time and Space Complexity

**Time Complexity** : O(n)
As we are moving in a linear motion in the array.

**Space Complexity** : O(1)
As we didn't use any extra memory such as an extra array , so the space complexity is O(1)

